I'm not suggesting to rewrite the AST, but to expose the existing AST in the same way that the JavaScript implementation does so: that is, allowing a user to pass in a function that accepts a document and returns a document. So, for instance:

```python
def transform_paragraph(paragraph):
    runs = mammoth.transforms.get_descendants_of_type(paragraph, Run)
    if runs and all(run.font in _monospace_fonts for run in runs):
        return paragraph.copy(style_id="code", style_name="Code")
    else:
        return paragraph

convert_to_html(document_transform=mammoth.transforms.paragraphs(transform_paragraph))
```

