So first off, you're right that it's `alternating_highway_lstm_cuda` -- `alternating_lstm_cuda` was never a thing.

I seem to have gotten the SRL model to train by doing the following:

1. create a new virtualenv or conda env for allennlp 0.4.3 (the last release prior to the 0.4 change that broke `alternating_highway_lstm_cuda`

```
conda create -n allennlp043 python=3.6
```

2. install allennlp 0.4.3

```
pip install allennlp==0.4.3
```

3. Use the following SRL config. It's exactly the same as https://github.com/allenai/allennlp/blob/v0.4.3/training_config/semantic_role_labeler.json , but i removed the `use_highway` argument and changed the encoder type to `"type": "alternating_highway_lstm_cuda"`.

```
{
  "dataset_reader":{"type":"srl"},
  "train_data_path": "conll-formatted-ontonotes-5.0-12/conll-formatted-ontonotes-5.0/data/train/",
  "validation_data_path": "conll-formatted-ontonotes-5.0-12/conll-formatted-ontonotes-5.0/data/development",
  "model": {
    "type": "srl",
    "text_field_embedder": {
      "tokens": {
        "type": "embedding",
        "embedding_dim": 100,
        "pretrained_file": "https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/allennlp/datasets/glove/glove.6B.100d.txt.gz",
        "trainable": true
      }
    },
    "initializer": [
      [
        "tag_projection_layer.*weight",
        {
          "type": "orthogonal"
        }
      ]
    ],
    "encoder": {
      "type": "alternating_highway_lstm_cuda",
      "input_size": 200,
      "hidden_size": 300,
      "num_layers": 8,
      "recurrent_dropout_probability": 0.1
    },
    "binary_feature_dim": 100
  },
  "iterator": {
    "type": "bucket",
    "sorting_keys": [["tokens", "num_tokens"]],
    "batch_size" : 80
  },

  "trainer": {
    "num_epochs": 500,
    "grad_clipping": 1.0,
    "patience": 20,
    "validation_metric": "+f1-measure-overall",
    "cuda_device": 0,
    "optimizer": {
      "type": "adadelta",
      "rho": 0.95
    }
  }
}
```

4. Train with the config however you normally would (e.g. `allennlp train <jsonpath> -s srl_test`.

