@ChrisBarker-NOAA , generally, it is a conda-env issue, not a conda bug.

In conda env create , when the specification is like channel::package, conda env does not parse it, and give it to conda. More importantly, the index that conda env got has no info about that channel.

As a result, when everything passed from condo-env to conda, it will raise exception

