@bhourigan Found the issue. In the main function, they attempt to check if the region passed to credstash will actual work here:
```python
try:
    region = args.region
    boto3.resource('dynamodb')
except botocore.exceptions.NoRegionError:
    region = DEFAULT_REGION
```
This is great, except they don't actually use the `region_name` parameter when they are checking the region, so, if there is no region defined in an environment variable or config file, it always falls back to `us-east-1` (like we were seeing). It looks like someone already opened a PR to fix this, so we should be good to go!

