@bukepo I like your suggestion to simplify the `ncp_base` but I think we may still need the lists in two places. (please let me know if I am missing something).

We need the `#ifdef` in either dispatcher `switch` or lookup table (we considered `switch` but decided for table instead  (the plan for future was to ensure the table keys are sorted so we can do a quick binary search)). 

We can define the handlers as functions under a namespace `Ncp` instead of a class member. Then I guess we need to declare them (as a prototype) in some header file (so we can use them). We can consider declaring all property handlers (without adding the `#ifdef`s in header file). Basically declare all handler functions, but then the definitions/implementations are tied to the `#ifdef` and the function uses are also tied to its `#ifdef`(from either the lookup table of `switch`). The thing is that it's still two places to add and maintain the lists.
